        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/20/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 09:48:42</font>

        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=471"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=471')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=8870&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Smart+Resistances%3F"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I put this out only as a bit of a head scratcher, not really as serious suggestion.</P><P>How is it that a character's spell resistances can tell if an incoming spell is harmful or benificial? Think about the warrior standing beside you, in his big shiny armor, every piece with +10 to every resistance under the sun. Would that not make them innately resistant to ALL spells? Are heals/buffs not spells? Should they not be resisted as well?</P><P>This of course would turn EQ on its ear, but it is fun to imagine the possiblities. </P><P>Cleric A says "CHeal on Tank A."<BR>Cleric A says "Dammit, what are you wearing? I cannot get CHeal to stick."<BR>Cleric A says "Ok, Necro A root that giant, so Tank A can pull back and strip while we get him healed."<BR>Necro A says "I will keep the giant busy, you do your thing."</P><P>Again, this is not really a suggestion, just something to get people's imaginations stimulated. What a world it would be. </P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>

